or=3D"#000099">and=20
equals <font color=3D"#CC0000">central angle ACB.<font color=3D"#000099"><b=
r>

Line AC (which also equals Line EC) is called the <font color=3D"#CC0000">c=
ircumradius <font color=3D"#000099"> (the radius of the outer,=20
circumscribed circle).<br>
Line DC is called the <font color=3D"#CC0000">inradius <font color=3D"#0000=
99"> or the <font color=3D"#CC0000"><i>apothem</i><font color=3D"#000099"> =
